# Git Lesson 2: Branching and Merging

## What is a Branch?
A branch in Git allows you to diverge from the main line of development and continue to do work without messing with that main line.

## Creating a Branch
To create a new branch:
```
git branch <branch-name>
```

## Switching Branches
To switch to a branch:
```
git checkout <branch-name>
```
Or, using the newer command:
```
git switch <branch-name>
```

## Creating and Switching in One Step
```
git checkout -b <branch-name>
```
Or:
```
git switch -c <branch-name>
```

## Merging Branches
To merge changes from another branch into your current branch:
```
git merge <branch-name>
```

## Deleting a Branch
After merging, you can delete a branch:
```
git branch -d <branch-name>
```

